Western Cape Premier Alan Winde speaks to eNCA to discuss the situation in the province.Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The ANC in the Western Cape wants an urgent return to Level 5 lockdown in the province but Premier Alan Winde says its too early to take such measures. Winde also believes the worst is yet to come for the province. READ: ANC Western Cape wants province to revert to Level 5 lockdown "You need to use data to say, this is why we should go to a different lockdown. We're doubling our numbers every 8 days. We know we'll move to 80,000 infections in one week." "I think it's unfounded. We'll have to slow down our hot spot areas. We've got to track and manage it but at the same time citizens must play their part." READ: COVID-19: SA cases rise to 8895, death toll at 178 The province has recorded nearly 4,500 COVID-19 infections. Watch the full interview with Western Cape Premier Alan Winde in the video above. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.